ent solar system bound. DPF may be able to place comparable constraint\non the massive gravity theories as the solar system bound. We also discuss the\nprospects of using eLISA and ASTROD-GW in testing alternative theories of\ngravity. The bounds using eLISA are similar to the LISA ones, but ASTROD-GW\nperforms the best in constraining massive gravity theories among all the\ngravitational wave detectors considered in this article.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Feb 2013 03:08:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-02-12"}
